					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2319859#post-2852026</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2319859/scp-3130#post-2852026</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 14 Jun 2017 07:43:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Modern_Erasmus</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3129691</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Eh, despite the addition of the mysterious figures this reads like a pretty standard reality bender from series 1. As someone else pointed out, despite being labeled as two individuals -1 is written as though it is only one, to the point of using the singular tense when describing their actions. Plus the reports of her loudly yelling stop suggesting reality suicide feels a bit ham fisted imo. Most importantly, I just didn't feel connected at all to the character.</p> <p>I think you've got something here, but it needs to be less 239 and more zena cho in terms of substance.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
